2.9
a) True because the addition operation is inside the parenthesis;
b) False because some of the variable name starts with underscores and consist of just symbols
c) False because division has an higher precedence than addition
d) False because a variable name cannot start with a number, cannot consist of two numbers and cannot have special characters like .,@


